        {
          "type": "section",
          "title": "#5: Correctness bug (RunVersion order) — CreateOrUpdateOrchestrator.cs",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "keyValue",
              "label": "Details",
              "pairs": {
                "Thread ID": "238146676",
                "Commenter": "David Fineboym",
                "File": "CreateOrUpdateOrchestrator.cs",
                "Category": "Correctness bug (RunVersion order)",
                "Action": "Acknowledged regression — will fix ordering",
                "Agent": "PR Author Assistant",
                "Reply Draft ID": "8528df1d-5c21-47a6-873d-bba232074602"
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "markdown",
              "label": "Original Comment",
              "body": "> This assignment should happen after `await UpsertDataProcessAsync`, as was before, otherwise on failure from backend, we will increase the run version not sequentially on retry. Because in finally block we patch SM resource including its metadata.\nFor example, backend has data-plane validation, so on bad input it will fail the request, customer can fix it, and re-PATCH the SM resource. Run Version is a customer visible column in target LAW table."
            },
            {
              "type": "markdown",
              "label": "AI Response",
              "body": "You're absolutely right — this is a correctness issue I introduced during the refactoring. The `internalMetadata.RunVersion = runVersion` assignment must happen **after** `await UpsertDataProcessAsync` succeeds, not before.\n\nAs you explained, the RunVersion gets persisted in the `finally` block when we patch the SM resource. If `UpsertDataProcessAsync` fails (e.g., backend data-plane validation), the incremented RunVersion would already be saved, and on retry with a scope change it would increment again — making RunVersion non-sequential for the customer-visible LAW table column.\n\nI'll move the assignment back to after `UpsertDataProcessAsync` as it was originally. Thanks for catching this — it's an important correctness guard."
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "label": "Code Context",
              "language": "diff",
              "filename": "CreateOrUpdateOrchestrator.cs",
              "body": "@@ CreateOrUpdateOrchestrator.cs - RunVersion assignment\n+            internalMetadata.RunVersion = runVersion;  // BUG: moved before UpsertDataProcessAsync\n+\n+            await UpsertDataProcessAsync(logger, context, ...)\n             // Should be: UpsertDataProcess first, THEN assign RunVersion"
            }
          ],
          "actions": [
            {
              "label": "Approve Reply",
              "style": "success",
              "command": {
                "type": "cli",
                "program": "pwsh",
                "args": [
                  "-Command",
                  "powerreview approve-draft --pr-url 'https://dev.azure.com/msazure/One/_git/ZTS/pullrequest/15337578' --draft-id '8528df1d-5c21-47a6-873d-bba232074602'"
                ]
              }
