        {
          "type": "section",
          "title": "#7: Error-forwarding design — CreateOrUpdateOrchestrator.cs",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "keyValue",
              "label": "Details",
              "pairs": {
                "Thread ID": "238151753",
                "Commenter": "David Fineboym",
                "File": "CreateOrUpdateOrchestrator.cs",
                "Category": "Error-forwarding design",
                "Action": "Agreed — will adopt caller-merge pattern",
                "Agent": "PR Author Assistant",
                "Reply Draft ID": "499187ba-693f-48f7-8c32-2513a566023e"
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "markdown",
              "label": "Original Comment",
              "body": "> The method accepts customerFacingError only to pass it through unchanged on the success path and replace it on the failure path. This makes the method responsible for error-forwarding logic that isn't its concern.\nThe more conventional approach is to have the method return only its own result and let the caller handle the merging.\n```\nfinally\n{\n    var (patchError, innerExceptionToRethrow) = await TryPatch...;\n    customerFacingError = patchError ?? customerFacingError;\n    ...\n}\n```"
            },
            {
              "type": "markdown",
              "label": "AI Response",
              "body": "You're right — the current signature makes `TryPatchSegmentationManagerAsync` responsible for error-forwarding logic that isn't really its concern. Accepting `customerFacingError` just to pass it through unchanged on success is unnecessary coupling.\n\nI'll refactor to your suggested pattern:\n\n```csharp\nfinally\n{\n    var (patchError, innerExceptionToRethrow) = await TryPatchSegmentationManagerAsync(...);\n    customerFacingError = patchError ?? customerFacingError;\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\nThis way the method only returns its own result (patch error or null), and the caller handles the merging. Cleaner separation of concerns."
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "label": "Code Context",
              "language": "diff",
              "filename": "CreateOrUpdateOrchestrator.cs",
              "body": "@@ CreateOrUpdateOrchestrator.cs - TryPatchSegmentationManagerAsync\n  private static async Task<(ErrorDefinition?, Exception?)>\n      TryPatchSegmentationManagerAsync(\n          ...\n-         ErrorDefinition? customerFacingError,  // pass-through coupling\n          ...)"
            }
          ],
          "actions": [
            {
              "label": "Approve Reply",
              "style": "success",
              "command": {
                "type": "cli",
                "program": "pwsh",
                "args": [
                  "-Command",
                  "powerreview approve-draft --pr-url 'https://dev.azure.com/msazure/One/_git/ZTS/pullrequest/15337578' --draft-id '499187ba-693f-48f7-8c32-2513a566023e'"
                ]
              }
            },
